resources.residConnectUpsellFlyoutText: You can see photos and videos from your devices, services, and social networks all in one place.  To get started, make sure you’re connected to the Internet.
resources.residEmptySourceMessage_EmptySourceView: All your photo sources are hidden. To show some, change your settings.
resources.residEmptySourceMessage_GenericDevice:
The Photos app shows you photos and videos from all your devices in one place.

To see photos and videos from another PC, go to that PC, go to SkyDrive.com/windows to download and install Microsoft SkyDrive, sign in with your Microsoft account, and then make sure to select the Fetch your files from anywhere setting.
resources.residEmptySourceMessage_Device: If you have any, make sure you’ve included them in your Pictures library of {{%1}}.
resources.residEmptySourceMessage_SkyDrive:
SkyDrive gives you free online storage for photos, videos and documents so you can access them from anywhere.

Go to SkyDrive.com to get started. Any photos and videos you store there will be shown here.
resources.residEmptySourceMessage_PicturesLibrary:
To get started, connect a device (camera, phone, USB flash drive, etc.), and import or copy photos and videos into your Pictures library.

If you already have photos or videos on this PC, make sure they’re in your Pictures library. You can manage your Pictures library from File Explorer.
resources.residCurrentlySyncingContent-extraInfo: This might take some time if you have a lot of photos.
